The paper discusses crowdsourcing, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to process data. The system presented, Reprowd, is designed to facilitate reproducibility in crowdsourced data processing research, which involves managing and analyzing large amounts of data (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the importance of social science in crowdsourcing, which falls under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the need for secure and trustworthy crowdsourcing, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CY).
